sentiment_score_definition: x <= -0.35: Bearish; -0.35 < x <= -0.15: Somewhat-Bearish; -0.15 < x < 0.15: Neutral; 0.15 <= x < 0.35: Somewhat_Bullish; x >= 0.35: Bullish
relevance_score_definition: 0 < x <= 1, with a higher score indicating higher relevance.

feed.title: Wyndham Hotels & Resorts, Inc. Announces Revision in Its Stock Evaluation Amid Financial Challenges

feed.title: BRBR CLASS ACTION REMINDER: Faruqi & Faruqi, LLP Reminds BellRing Brands (BRBR) Investors ...
feed.summary: Faruqi & Faruqi, LLP has reminded investors of BellRing Brands (BRBR) about a class action lawsuit filed against the company. The lawsuit alleges that BellRing and its executives violated federal securities laws by making false or misleading statements regarding the company's sales growth and the impact of competition. Investors who suffered losses between November 19, 2024, and August 4, 2025, are encouraged to contact the firm by the March 26, 2026 deadline to discuss their legal options and potentially seek the role of lead plaintiff.

feed.title: TopBuild Posts Q4 2025 Results, Highlights Acquisition-Driven Growth

feed.title: New Anterix-Qualcomm chips aim to harden the power grid with 4G and 5G links
feed.summary: Anterix (NASDAQ: ATEX) has expanded its collaboration with Qualcomm to hasten the deployment of next-generation private wireless connectivity for utilities. This partnership, focusing on Qualcomm's Snapdragon SDX35-3 and SDX32-3 IoT Modems, will deliver 4G and 5G cellular connectivity over Anterix’s 900 MHz broadband platform, enhancing grid modernization and resilience. Eight utilities have already adopted Anterix-enabled private wireless, with the initiative further supported by the FCC's expansion of the 900 MHz band.

feed.title: Anterix Deepens Collaboration with Qualcomm to Accelerate Utility Grid Connectivity
feed.summary: Anterix is expanding its collaboration with Qualcomm Technologies Inc. to accelerate the adoption of next-generation connectivity for utilities and critical infrastructure, focusing on private wireless broadband. This partnership aims to provide utilities with a scalable path to 5G, enabling enhanced operational visibility, resilience, and grid modernization through new industrial-grade IoT chipsets optimized for utility use cases. The initiative highlights Anterix's role in advancing beyond spectrum access to a complete private wireless connectivity platform for the sector.

feed.title: Health Care Q4 Dividend Roundup: Merck Offers Thicker Dividend Cushion Than AbbVie
feed.summary: Merck & Co. has been upgraded to a "buy" due to an improving dividend cushion ratio (DCR) and strong Q4 2025 earnings, with a projected 2026 DCR of 2.57x. In contrast, AbbVie faces DCR pressure from CAPEX plans, despite strong results, with a projected 2026 DCR of 2.19x. While AbbVie has a lower forward P/E, dividend yields suggest different valuation dynamics between the two pharmaceutical giants.

feed.title: Viatris beats on Q4; eyes 10% staff reduction (VTRS:NASDAQ)

feed.title: Chubb Limited Board Will Recommend 33rd Consecutive Annual Dividend Increase to Shareholders at the 2026 Annual General Meeting; Declares Quarterly Dividend
